Integration tests for `ctx_cage::cli::resolve_mode`, exercising the mapping from `Cli` flags to `Mode` (or `ResolveError`) without touching clap or the filesystem, except `--task-file` which reads a real tempfile.

Provides two test-only helpers: `fresh_tempfile(label) -> PathBuf` (unique path under the OS tempdir, keyed by an atomic counter + pid, caller must delete) and `base(target) -> Cli` (a `Cli` with every flag at default, used as a builder base per test). These helpers encode the current `Cli`/`TaskFlags`/`SpendFlags` field layout directly (no `..Default::default()`), so adding a field to those structs requires updating `base()` here too or the crate fails to build.

Documents `resolve_mode`'s contract via cases, which is the real spec surface if `cli.rs` changes: self-test mode never requires spend approval; interactive/task modes require `allow_spend=true` or return `ResolveError::NotAllowed`; `--task` and `--task-file` together, `--self-test` with `--task`, and `--task` with `--interactive` are all `ResolveError::Conflict`; `--task-file` content becomes the `Mode::Task` string verbatim (including trailing newline).